Name of Quantlet: CRIX-Style Crypto Basket Construction
Description:
This Quantlet constructs a CRIX-style cryptocurrency basket using a data-driven constituent selection rule. Instead of using a fixed top-5 cryptocurrency basket, the project applies a liquidity-coverage style methodology to determine the number of basket constituents from the data.
The analysis uses daily price and volume data for a 20-token cryptocurrency universe from Yahoo Finance. At each monthly rebalance date, tokens are ranked by a 90-day average market-cap proxy, calculated as daily close price multiplied by a snapshot circulating supply. The basket then selects the smallest number of tokens required to cover at least 90% of the total market-cap proxy.
The project compares the resulting liquidity-coverage equal-weight basket with BTC, ETH, fixed top-5 equal-weight, and fixed top-5 cap-weight basket designs. The analysis includes index construction, rolling correlation, downside risk comparison, correlation heatmaps, MDS visualization, BTC beta regression, and tail-dependence analysis during BTC crash days.

