## Notes

This Quantlet implements the liquidity-coverage style component of a CRIX-inspired methodology. The full CRIX methodology also includes an information criterion component, which is not implemented here. The focus of this notebook is on data-driven constituent selection, basket construction, and comparison across alternative crypto index designs.

The market-cap proxy is based on close prices and snapshot circulating supply. Therefore, it should be interpreted as an approximate ranking measure rather than an exact historical market capitalization series.

## Expected Result

The notebook shows that a data-driven crypto basket can provide a more flexible index construction framework than a fixed top-5 basket. The selected number of constituents changes over time, which supports the idea that crypto index methodology should adapt to market structure rather than rely on a fixed constituent count.
